headline: 1 Consumer Stock to Own for Decades and 2 to Avoid
summary: Most consumer discretionary businesses succeed or fail based on the broader economy. This sensitive demand profile can cause the industry to stumble when macro uncertainty enters the fray, and over the past six months, its returns were flat. This performance was similar to the S&P 500.
